      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHARP INTEREST (10) made a nice return at her latest appearance nine days ago, finishing 2.5 metres away in second over 1609m at Charlton. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Meets a similar line up so she is capable of getting the job done. MASTER MIKI (11) has been racing extra well and again did a good job last start when runner-up at this track over 1690m, beaten 3.5 metres after settling at the rear of the field then working into the race strongly prior to cornering. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Meets a comparable field and he can add to the solid recent record. HEZ HARRYWHO (8) is worth another chance after a last-start eighth over 1690m at this track two weeks ago. COLORADO GIRL (6) is worth some thought based on her second over 1609m at Cranbourne two runs ago.",
